{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"trim-lop-azure","description":"# Split build_server() (703-LOC single function) into tool registrars\n\n## What\n`mcp_server.py:295-997` is one ~703-LOC function of ~40 `@server.tool` closures — the longest function in the tree. Split into `register_read_tools(server, …)` / `register_write_tools(server, …)` / `register_llm_tools(server, …)` grouped by the existing read/write/LLM taxonomy; `build_server` discovers + wires them. Lift the `run_workflow` background-orchestration and `reconcile` mode-gating out of the tool bodies.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `build_server` delegates to per-cluster registrars; each registrar is on-target size (200-400 LOC).\n- [ ] The MCP tool set + gating (readonly/allow_llm/allow_jira_sync) are unchanged (coverage test green).\n- [ ] `make lint` + MCP suites pass; commit carries a `rebar-ticket:` trailer.","id":"16df-766a-7d57-4213","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Split build_server() (703-LOC single function) into tool registrars"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783056807658099001,"uuid":"8ee2ade1-07e3-4040-bf06-88f4a9627028"}